meaning_str.bing:
n. 赝品；假货；冒充者
v. 伪造；假装；冒充
adj. 假的；冒充的；伪造的
网络. 假动作；膺品；做假动作

假货；骗局；诡计；欺骗行为；假动作（体育比赛中用以迷惑对手）；伪装
伪造的；假的；仿制的；虚假的；欺骗性的；不真实的；冒充的
伪造；假装；欺骗；（在体育比赛中）做假动作以迷惑对手；佯装；装出（某种感情、有病等）；冒充

1.en: Like the oil overhang, when those inventories get 'mined, ' prices will likely suffer, transforming the head fake into a major headache.
1.cn: 与石油过剩一样，当这些库存被利用起来时，价格也可能会大幅下跌，将这种假象转变为真正的头痛。

2.en: The trick was that three of the four fake players contributed reasonably to the kitty and took only a fair share, while the fourth did not.
2.cn: 花招在于四个伪玩家中的三个适当捐献公共储金，并且只取走公平的份额，而第四个玩家不同。

3.en: He said the suspected bomber has not been identified, but was carrying a fake driver's license from the U. S. state of Michigan.
3.cn: 他表示，还没有确认袭击者的身份，但此人携带伪造的美国密西根州的驾驶执照。

0.en: Cause you know that's all fake. It's all done on a computer? It's like that video, what is it?
0.cn: 这些可都是假的，是电脑特效，就像那个视频一样，什么来着？

1.en: Look at these authentic fake medals. I tell you, mom's gonna be voted best dressed at the make-believe military academy.
1.cn: 瞧瞧这些假徽章，妈会得到“最佳服装奖”在假的军校里。

2.en: It's all a fugazi. You know what a fugazi is? Uh. Fugayzi. It's a fake. Fugayzi, fugazi, it's a whazy, it's a woozy, it's...
2.cn: 这都是忽悠人的，你知道什么是忽悠吧，忽悠，就是假的。忽悠来，忽悠去。

3.en: We had one of those silly fake weddings.
3.cn: 办了那种傻傻的假婚礼。

4.en: Gotta be a pretty good fake to fool Glasses.
4.cn: 能骗过眼镜儿，肯定够逼真啊。

5.en: You'll have to fake it. Lady Mary, Edith, Mr Branson...
5.cn: 你们只能装装了，玛丽小姐，伊迪丝，布兰森先生…

6.en: Max, you do fake stairs so well. I know. It's the second best thing I fake.
6.cn: 麦克斯，你好会演假装下楼梯。我知道，这是我"假"得第二好的事。

7.en: I'm just saying, if we fake got back together, that's totally not how it fake happened.
7.cn: 我只是想说，如果我们假装和好，那也肯定不是这么和好的。

8.en: I don't believe this. You got him to pretend he was some fake doctor? Fake? Excuse me? Hello?
8.cn: 我不敢相信，你要他假扮医生？假扮？对不起，喂。

9.en: Hey, Mr. Phillips. Nice suit. Right there. That was so fake!
9.cn: 嘿，菲利浦先生，很好看的西装。抓到了，真是好假！

10.en: Nikita doesn't have time to fake that. There's too much heat.
10.cn: 尼基塔没时间伪造这种文件。风声太紧了

11.en: But when I'd ask him where they were, he'd give me a fake address.
11.cn: 可每次我问他派对在哪里，他都会给我假地址。

12.en: Then she moved to England and she picked up this fake British accent.
12.cn: 后来她搬去英国了，还学了假惺惺的英国口音。

13.en: Now you think I wouldn't enjoy that, because it is so fake, but I still do.
13.cn: 你以为你说得太假，我会不相信，但我还是觉得很高兴。

14.en: I didn't care if they were real or fake. It was a great way to pass the time.
14.cn: 我不在乎故事的真假，这是个消磨时光的好办法。

15.en: The Internet. She gets a fake ID, she sends money to herself. What does this mean?
15.cn: 网络。她制造假身份，给自己汇钱。这是什么意思？

16.en: You were just being so nice to him. I was faking it. Can't you tell when I'm being fake?
16.cn: 你看起来跟他很好啊。我是装出来的，你难道看不出来我是装的吗？

17.en: Maybe. Or maybe hiding behind a fake screenname gives the people the courage to go negative.
17.cn: 也许吧，又或者藏在网名的假面之后让人有勇气去攻击别人。

18.en: I'm not gonna make a fake appointment with a psychiatrist. What would I say is wrong with me?
18.cn: 我才不要假装病人去看精神科医生，我要假装有啥毛病呢？

19.en: This is so exciting. Soon, my upper lip will be the same fake blonde as my beautiful best friend.
19.cn: 好兴奋哦，我唇上的汗毛很快会跟我美丽好友一样有着好看的假金色了。
